<TITLE> Govt shuffles civil servants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)- Hafizur Rahman Bhuiyan, chairman of Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation, has been appointed to Rajshahi as its divisional commissioner, according to a circular released by the establishment ministry Monday. There have been other changes and appointments on deputation at different levels of the administration, according to separate establishment ministry circulars. Dhaka Transport Coordination Board director Sultanuddin Ahmed has been made deputy secretary to the Planning Division. Planning Division deputy secretary Fakhrul Islam has been made officer on special duty (OSD), and Md Helaluddin of the Board of Investment has been transferred as deputy secretary to the religious affairs ministry. OSD deputy secretary Mohammad Alauddin has been made director of BIAM Foundation, deputy secretary (OSD) Subhashish Basu has been appointed secretary of the BoI. Director at the Chief Adviser's Officer Khorshed Alam Chowdhury has been made director of Dhaka Transport Coordination Board and deputy secretary of the religious affairs ministry Fayezur Rahman Faruqui has been appointed to Bangladesh Television additional director. Senior warrant officer of the Bangladesh Army Amar Bihari Biswas has been appointed foreman of the BRTC on deputation. Abul Kalam, who had worked for BRTC in the same post, was taken back to his previous post of army warrant officer. The contractual appointment of Bangladesh ambassador to the United Arab Emirates, ATM Nazimullah Chowdhury, has been extended by three months. Syed Nasir Ershad, private secretary to the secretary of the local government division, has been appointed first secretary (labour) at the Bangladesh embassy in South Korea. bdnew
